HARSHAD NUMBERS : A Harshad number (also called a Niven number) is a number that is divisible by the sum of its digits.

Example : Number = 18

Digits: 1 + 8 = 9

18 รท 9 = 2
            So, 18 is a Harshad number


PROGRAM:
public class HarshadNumbers {  

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		int n=21;
		int result=0,temp;
		while(n!=0) {
			temp=n%10;
			result=result+temp;
			n=n/10;
		}
    if(n%result==0)
    {
    	System.out.println("It is Harshad Number");
    }
    else
    {
    	System.out.println("Not a Harshad Number");
    }
	}

}
